  "text": "RADARSAT-2 images were regrouped by their incidence angle, keeping differences no longer than 4 degrees between them, as pointed out by Baghdadi et al. [CITATION_1] . Two groups of images combined from their incidence angle were analyzed separately: FQ12 (32°) with FQ16 (36°), and FQ16 (36°) with FQ20 (40°).",
